  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Staff Nurse @ Senior Care Centre",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Purpose:</strong></u></p><p>Do you want to make a difference in someone else’s life as a staff nurse? Active Global wants YOU to be part of our family!</p><p><u><strong>Job Description:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Key person in setting up and upkeep of clinical/medical protocols pertaining to client needs, from onboarding to discharging.</li><li>Assessment for new case referrals and reassessment of existing clients.</li><li>Guide, train and leading a team of Healthcare Assistants and oversee the nursing care, standards and operations across our day care centres.</li><li>Working closely with other healthcare professionals on planning client ICP, care and safety in the centre.</li><li>Respond to emergencies, conduct investigations on incidents and preventive actions.</li><li>Working with the centre management on ensuring the upkeep of clinical equipment and supplies.</li><li>Evaluate and monitor progress of clients’ treatment regularly. </li><li>Ensure strict compliance to MOH regulations in the performance of services. </li><li>Create and maintain database of all clients, ensuring strict compliance to documentation, providing evidence-based treatment with accurate and timely records.  </li><li>Any other adhoc tasks assigned by the management.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Requirements:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Minimum NITEC / Diploma / Bachelor’s Degree in Nursing.</li><li>Advanced Diploma in Gerontology or Palliative Care is an advantage.</li><li>Must be an Enrolled Nurse or Registered Nurse with Singapore Nursing Board and possess a clean disciplinary record (nurses on conditional licenses are not eligible for this role).</li><li>Minimum 2 years of clinical experience.</li><li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office and comfortable using IT tools in daily work.</li><li>Ability to converse in local dialects will be an added advantage due to elderly clients in eldercare sector.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Benefits:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Attractive base salary and incentives for driving results.</li><li>Opportunities for professional training and career development within the organization.</li><li>Health Insurance Coverage.</li><li>Industry-specific training and mentorship from a highly experienced team.</li><li>Supportive and flexible work environment that encourages innovation and process improvement.</li><li>15 days annual leave.</li><li>Performance based bonus.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Working Location:</strong></u></p><ul><li>Sengkang West, Fernvale Glades</li></ul>",
